{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y8jGJsuo26XNccvzNpXS7u","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: add-view\n     3→description: Add a new API view function or endpoint to a Django views.py file. Use when adding views, endpoints, or API routes.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Add View\n     7→\n     8→Add a new API view function to views.py using jig.\n     9→\n    10→## Usage\n    11→\n    12→Run the jig recipe with `view_name` and `model_name`:\n    13→\n    14→```bash\n    15→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"view_name\": \"<name>\", \"model_name\": \"<Model>\"}'\n    16→```\n    17→\n    18→If invoked as `/add-view <view_name> <model_name>`:\n    19→\n    20→```bash\n    21→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\"view_name\": \"$1\", \"model_name\": \"$2\"}'\n    22→```\n    23→\n    24→## Variables\n    25→\n    26→- **view_name**: The function name (e.g. `reservation_receipt`)\n    27→- **model_name**: The Django model to query (e.g. `Reservation`)\n    28→\n    29→Extract these from the user's request. For \"add a receipt view for Reservation\", that's `view_name: reservation_receipt`, `model_name: Reservation`.\n    30→\n    31→## Gotchas\n    32→\n    33→- If jig exits non-zero, it prints the rendered template to stderr. Use that output to apply changes manually.\n    34→- Run `jig vars ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/recipe.yaml` to confirm required variables if unsure.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dff2ea0d-f49d-4b98-8ef9-32c17c8cdd82","uuid":"84d0ea06-8795-459f-adc1-d9e54034cefc"}
